//
// test/lsp/fixtures/folding_parse_error.nsl - exercises folding's
// partial-AST handling per folding-range.contract.md §6 (FR-017).
// The outer `module m {` opens cleanly and the inner `func f { ... }`
// closes cleanly, but the file is missing the outer `}` so the M2
// parser drops into error-recovery and produces a partial AST.
// FoldingRangeBuilder must walk what the parser DID recognize
// (every block-opener carries a valid SourceRange) and emit folds
// for them — without crashing or returning a JSON-RPC error.

module m {
  func f {
    a = b;
  }
  func g {
    c = d;
  }
// missing outer `}` here — the file ends before the module closes.
